This is a known breaking change. Android 15 (API 35) — which .NET 10 targets — **deprecated and ignores** `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE`. Edge-to-edge is now enforced, so you must use **WindowInsets** to react to the keyboard.

## Quick fix: `adjustPan`

If you just need something working fast, set this in `Platforms/Android/AndroidManifest.xml` on your `<activity>`:

```xml
android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustPan"
```

This pans the whole view up but gives you less control.

## Recommended fix: Handle IME insets

For a chat UI, you want to shrink the content area. Add a listener for IME insets in your `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Find the root MAUI view and listen for inset changes
        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new InsetsListener());
    }

    private class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of IME or nav bar bottom inset
            int bottomPadding = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navBarInsets.Bottom);

            view.SetPadding(
                view.PaddingLeft,
                view.PaddingTop,
                view.PaddingRight,
                bottomPadding);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

This listens for keyboard (IME) show/hide and adjusts the bottom padding of your root view, pushing your input bar above the keyboard — exactly what `Resize` used to do.

**Key points:**
- `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` gives you the keyboard height
- The nav bar inset ensures correct spacing when the keyboard is hidden
- No changes needed in your XAML layout
